# 3. Design — Clinical Luxury Brand Identity
# 3. Design System & Brand Identity

Strictly enforce the **"Morning Spa" / Medical Luxury** brand identity. Full documentation in **`DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`** in this repo.

## Brand Pillars
Every component and flow must align with at least one of these four pillars:
1. **Resilience** — Medical authority, dermatologist-approved
2. **Transparency** — Clear pricing, honest ingredients
3. **Refinement** — Understated luxury, elegant details
4. **Empathy** — Warm, nurturing, approachable

## Color Palette (Tailwind Tokens)

All colors are defined in `tailwind.config.ts`. **Never use pure white (#FFF) or pure black (#000).**

### Primary Canvas
- `asper-stone` (`#F2EFEB`) — Main background, cards
- `asper-stone-light` (`#F8F6F3`) — Lightest variant
- `asper-stone-dark` (`#E8E4DE`) — Subtle contrast

### Feminine Softness
- `rose-clay` (`#C4A494`) — Warm accents, secondary backgrounds
- `rose-clay-light` (`#D4B8A8`) — Hover states, delicate elements
- `rose-clay-dark` (`#A88B7A`) — Deeper terracotta

### Primary Actions & Authority
- `burgundy` (`#6B2D3A`) — Primary buttons, CTAs, navigation
- `burgundy-light` (`#8B3D4A`) — Hover states
- `burgundy-dark` (`#4F222C`) — Active states

### Accent
- `polished-gold` (`#C9A962`) — Borders, icons, badges (use sparingly)

### Text
- `asper-ink` (`#2C2825`) — Primary body text, headings
- `asper-ink-muted` (`#5C5652`) — Secondary text, captions

### Utility
- `polished-white` (`#FAF9F7`) — Off-white for cards on colored backgrounds

## Typography

Defined in `tailwind.config.ts`:
- **Headings:** `font-heading` → Playfair Display (serif, elegant)
- **Body:** `font-body` → Montserrat (sans-serif, clinical precision)
- **Arabic:** `font-arabic` → Tajawal (RTL bilingual support)

## Component Standards

## Design System Tokens

**Tailwind CSS:** Use the Clinical Luxury palette from `tailwind.config.ts`:
- **Primary canvas:** `asper-stone` (#F2EFEB) — warm ivory/light gray, no pure #FFF
- **Feminine softness:** `rose-clay` (#C4A494) — muted pink/terracotta
- **Primary actions/nav/authority:** `burgundy` (#6B2D3A) — deep burgundy
- **Accent only:** `polished-gold` (#C9A962) — borders, hover ("Midas Touch"), icons
- **Background highlight:** `polished-white` (#FAF9F7) — softer alternative to pure white
- **Primary text:** `asper-ink` (#2C2825) — no pure #000
- **Muted text:** `asper-ink-muted` (#5C5652)

Each color has `DEFAULT`, `light`, and `dark` variants (except polished-gold and polished-white).

## Four Design Pillars

Every component, page, and user flow must embody at least one pillar:

1. **Resilience:** Empowers customers overcoming skin challenges (acne, rosacea, hyperpigmentation). Show progress, hope, and transformation.
2. **Transparency:** Honest ingredient lists, clear pricing (no hidden fees), authentic product info. Build trust through openness.
3. **Refinement:** Luxury aesthetics—elegant typography (Playfair Display headings, Montserrat body), smooth animations (luxury easing), tasteful gold accents. Every detail polished.
4. **Empathy:** Clinical yet caring tone. Address skin concerns with understanding. Personalized AI recommendations that listen first.

## Copy & Tone

- **Authoritative and clinical** where needed (ingredient science, dermatological claims).
- **Empathetic and supportive** for skin conditions (acne, rosacea).
- **Transparent** pricing and ingredients—no hidden costs, no misleading claims.
- Avoid generic wellness buzzwords; be specific and evidence-based.

## Configuration

For environment or build config related to UI and deployment, refer to **APPLY_TO_MAIN_SITE.md** in this repo.
### Buttons
- **Primary:** `bg-burgundy text-white hover:bg-burgundy-light rounded-md px-6 py-3 font-body font-semibold`
- **Secondary:** `border-2 border-burgundy text-burgundy bg-transparent hover:bg-burgundy hover:text-white`
- **Gold Accent:** Use sparingly — `border-2 border-polished-gold`

### Cards
- Background: `bg-asper-stone` or `bg-polished-white`
- Border: `border border-rose-clay-light` (optional)
- Radius: `rounded-lg` (12px)
- Shadow: `shadow-maroon-glow` (custom shadow)
- Padding: `p-6` (desktop), `p-4` (mobile)

### Navigation
- Background: `bg-burgundy`
- Text: `text-white`
- Active/hover: `text-polished-gold`

### Inputs
- Background: `bg-polished-white`
- Border: `border border-rose-clay`
- Focus: `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-polished-gold focus:border-polished-gold`

## Animations

All use custom `luxury` easing: `cubic-bezier(0.19, 1, 0.22, 1)`
- `animate-fade-in` — Fade in with upward movement
- `animate-fade-up` — Pronounced upward fade
- `animate-shake` — Error emphasis
- `animate-skeleton-breathe` — Loading states

## Accessibility Requirements
- WCAG AA contrast standards for all text
- Visible focus rings on all interactive elements: `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-polished-gold`
- Minimum 44×44px touch targets on mobile
- Semantic HTML with proper heading hierarchy

## Design Implementation Checklist
Before committing any UI changes:
- [ ] Uses only approved color palette (no pure #FFF or #000)
- [ ] Applies correct font families (`font-heading`, `font-body`)
- [ ] Uses `rounded-md` or `rounded-lg` for border radius
- [ ] Adds `shadow-maroon-glow` for elevated elements
- [ ] Includes hover and focus states for interactive elements
- [ ] Tests responsive behavior on mobile
- [ ] Verifies WCAG AA contrast ratios
- [ ] Aligns with at least one brand pillar

## Copy Guidelines
- **Clinical authority:** Medical terminology where appropriate, dermatologist-approved language
- **Empathetic tone:** Sensitive approach to skin conditions (acne, rosacea, hyperpigmentation)
- **Transparency:** Clear pricing, honest ingredient lists, no hidden fees
- **Bilingual support:** RTL layout for Arabic content using `font-arabic`

Reference **`DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`** for complete specifications, code examples, and visual guidelines.

